In this memorandum from July 17, 2009, President Barack Obama assigns certain reporting functions under the Supplemental Appropriations Act, 2009 to various officials. The functions include providing reports and information to Congress. The Attorney General is assigned the responsibility of providing specific reports and a plan to Congress. The Director of National Intelligence, in consultation with the Secretary of Defense, is assigned the responsibility of providing a report to Congress. The Secretary of State, also in consultation with the Secretary of Defense, is assigned the responsibility of providing information to Congress. The memorandum concludes by authorizing and directing the Attorney General to publish the memorandum in the Federal Register.